Vice President Biden will be traveling to China, Mongolia, and Japan on August 16, 2011. He will visit China at the invitation of Vice President Xi Jinping. In China, he will meet with Vice President Xi, President Hu, and Premier Wen Jiabao to discuss various bilateral, regional, and global issues. He will also visit the city of Chengdu. In Mongolia, the Vice President will show support for their democratic development and growing economic ties. In Japan, he will express U.S. support after the recent earthquake, tsunami, and nuclear emergency. He will thank U.S. civilian and military personnel for their assistance and highlight Japan's resilience during the recovery process. More details about the trip will be released later.